#: ../../spinningup/exercises.rst:119
msgid ""
"The hardest part of writing RL code is dealing with bugs, because "
"failures are frequently silent. The code will appear to run correctly, "
"but the agent's performance will degrade relative to a bug-free "
"implementation---sometimes to the extent that it never learns anything."
msgstr ""
"撰寫強化學習 (Reinforcement Learning, RL) 程式碼最困難的部分是處理錯誤，"
"因為失敗經常是靜默的。程式碼看起來會正常運行，但智能體 (Agent) 的效能會"
"相對於無錯誤的實作有所下降——有時甚至到完全學不到任何東西的程度。"

#: ../../spinningup/exercises.rst:121
msgid ""
"In this exercise, you will observe a bug in vivo and compare results "
"against correct code. The bug is the same (conceptually, if not in exact "
"implementation) for both the PyTorch and Tensorflow versions of this "
"exercise."
msgstr ""
"在這個練習中，你將觀察一個實際運行中的錯誤，並將結果與正確的程式碼進行比較。"
"這個錯誤在 PyTorch 和 Tensorflow 版本中概念上是相同的（即使具體實作可能不同）。"

#: ../../spinningup/exercises.rst:123
msgid ""
"**Instructions.** Run ``exercise2_2.py``, which will launch DDPG "
"experiments with and without a bug. The non-bugged version runs the "
"default Spinning Up implementation of DDPG, using a default method for "
"creating the actor and critic networks. The bugged version runs the same "
"DDPG code, except uses a bugged method for creating the networks."
msgstr ""
"**說明。** 執行 ``exercise2_2.py``，它將啟動有錯誤和無錯誤的 DDPG 實驗。"
"無錯誤版本使用 Spinning Up 預設的 DDPG 實作，採用預設方法建立演員 (Actor) "
"和評論家 (Critic) 網路。有錯誤版本執行相同的 DDPG 程式碼，但使用有缺陷的"
"方法建立網路。"

#: ../../spinningup/exercises.rst:125
msgid ""
"There will be six experiments in all (three random seeds for each case), "
"and each should take in the ballpark of 10 minutes. When they're "
"finished, plot the results. What is the difference in performance with "
"and without the bug?"
msgstr ""
"總共會有六個實驗（每種情況三個隨機種子），每個大約需要 10 分鐘。"
"完成後，繪製結果。有錯誤和無錯誤的效能差異是什麼？"

#: ../../spinningup/exercises.rst:127
msgid ""
"Without referencing the correct actor-critic code (which is to say---"
"don't look in DDPG's ``core.py`` file), try to figure out what the bug is"
" and explain how it breaks things."
msgstr ""
"在不參考正確的 actor-critic 程式碼的情況下（也就是說——不要查看 DDPG 的 "
"``core.py`` 檔案），嘗試找出錯誤是什麼，並解釋它如何破壞了運作。"

#: ../../spinningup/exercises.rst:129
msgid ""
"**Hint.** To figure out what's going wrong, think about how the DDPG code"
" implements the DDPG computation graph. For the Tensorflow version, look "
"at this excerpt:"
msgstr ""
"**提示。** 要找出問題所在，思考一下 DDPG 程式碼是如何實作 DDPG 計算圖的。"
"對於 Tensorflow 版本，請看以下摘錄："

#: ../../spinningup/exercises.rst:140
msgid "How could a bug in the actor-critic code have an impact here?"
msgstr "actor-critic 程式碼中的錯誤如何能在此處產生影響？"

#: ../../spinningup/exercises.rst:142
msgid ""
"**Bonus.** Are there any choices of hyperparameters which would have "
"hidden the effects of the bug?"
msgstr ""
"**額外題。** 是否有任何超參數的選擇可以隱藏該錯誤的影響？"

